<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN299">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>parutti vēlic cīṟūr maṉṉa</l>
<l>ṉuḻuttata ruṇṭa vōynaṭaip puravi</l>
<l>kaṭaṉmaṇṭu tōṇiyiṟ paṭaimukam pōḻa</l>
<l>neymmiti yaruntiya koycuva leruttiṟ</l>
<l>ṟaṇṇaṭai maṉṉar tāruṭaip puravi</l>
<l>yaṇaṅkuṭai murukaṉ kōṭṭattuk</l>
<l>kalantoṭā makaḷiri ṉikaḻntuniṉ ṟavvē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The king of the little village fenced with cotton,</l>
<l>while [his] horses with tired gait that had eaten blackgram husks</l>
<l>cut into the army front like boats thrusting into the sea,</l>
<l>the garlanded horses of the king’s of paddy-producing villages,</l>
<l>their necks with trimmed manes, that had fed on ghee[-soaked] food balls,</l>
<l>they stood [still], despised by the women who do not touch ornaments</l>
<l>in the enclosure of dreadful Murukaṉ.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
